<h2 class="wp-block-heading">General</h2>



<p>This is the accessibility statement for the Generation AI project. The website <strong>www.generation-ai-stn.fi</strong> is subject to the Finnish Act on the Provision of Digital Services, which requires public online services to be accessible. This statement concerns the website <strong>www.generation-ai-stn.fi</strong>. It was originally prepared on 28 August 2023 and updated on 20 March 2026 based on a manual WCAG 2.1 AA audit, implemented accessibility fixes, and automated regression testing with Playwright and axe-core.</p>



<h2 class="wp-block-heading">Status of the digital service's accessibility</h2>



<p>The digital service is <strong>fully compliant</strong> with WCAG 2.1 level AA requirements. A manual audit carried out in March 2026 identified issues that have since been fixed. After the fixes, the site was covered with automated Playwright + axe-core WCAG 2.1 AA regression tests.</p>

<p>The latest automated test run was carried out on 20 March 2026. It covered 11 representative pages across the Finnish, English and Swedish sections of the site, including the home page, key main navigation sections, material pages, and publication and document layouts. The test run did not detect any WCAG 2.1 level A or AA issues.</p>

<p>On the same day, a separate styling regression was identified on the <code>/materiaalit/</code> page, where button-like links could inherit an incorrect text color. The issue was fixed by narrowing the shared text-link color rule, and a dedicated Playwright regression test was added to verify the intended button colors on the materials page.</p>

<p>In addition, the desktop <code>About the project</code> mega menu was fixed so that it always stays within the visible browser viewport, including near the right edge of the screen. A dedicated Playwright regression test was added for this behavior as well.</p>

<h2 class="wp-block-heading">Assessment methods</h2>

<p>The accessibility of the service has been assessed by manual code review and by automated browser-based testing using Playwright and axe-core. Separate regression checks are also used for button links on the materials page and for the desktop mega menu position within the viewport.</p>



<h2 class="wp-block-heading">Accessibility feedback</h2>



<p>If you notice accessibility problems on the website, please send feedback by email to <a href="mailto:info@generation-ai-stn.fi">info@generation-ai-stn.fi</a>.</p>



<h2 class="wp-block-heading">Supervisory authority</h2>



<p>If you are not satisfied with the response you receive, or if you do not receive a response within 14 days, you may file a complaint with the Regional State Administrative Agency for Southern Finland. <a href="https://www.saavutettavuusvaatimukset.fi/oikeutesi/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">Read more on the authority website<span class="sr-only"> (opens in a new tab)</span></a>.</p>



